						               													<description>This game was published in the wake of the best-selling success of Dr. Peter's book &amp;quot;The Peter Principle&amp;quot; (oft-quoted as &amp;quot;In a hierarchy, every employee tends to rise to his or her level of incompetence&amp;quot;). In it, the players, employees of a huge corporation, compete to avoid promotion and remain competent (by taking more &amp;quot;right&amp;quot; decisions than &amp;quot;wrong&amp;quot; ones). At the same time, each tries to force the others into promotion or into &amp;quot;deadwood&amp;quot; status (which happens by accumulating enough wrong decisions and being found out). The last player still alive and competent is declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game was originally published by Skor-Mor in 1973, but the 1981 AH edition is much easier to find.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Skor-Mor published 3D puzzles and games in clear plastic such as Chess in the Third Dimension and a 3D Tic-Tac-Toe called Trinary. It disappeared in the early 1980s.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A related game, theme-wise, is AH's Bureaucracy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
